.TH MEMBERVARS 1 "March 2026" "membervars 1.0.3" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
membervars \- convert member variable naming conventions
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B membervars
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fIfiles...\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBmembervars\fR rewrites source files in place to convert member variable
identifier styles.
.PP
It supports two conversion modes:
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fBm_<name>\fR to \fB<name>_\fR
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fB<name>_\fR to \fBm_<name>\fR
.PP
Replacements are skipped in comments, string literals, and character literals.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-u
Convert member vars from \fBm_<name>\fR to \fB<name>_\fR.
.TP
.B \-m
Convert member vars from \fB<name>_\fR to \fBm_<name>\fR.
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-verbose
Increase logging verbosity.
.TP
.B \-q, \-\-quiet
Decrease logging verbosity.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show help text.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Show tool version.
